README
======

1. Create a new container to serve as the host:

   `sudo lxc-create -n decc -t ubuntu`

2. Start the container:

   `sudo lxc-start -n decc -d`

3. Now on the container we need to ensure we have some tools. Use this:

   `sudo lxc-attach -n decc`

4. On the container, setup ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
   so that you can login without requiring a password for the 'ubuntu' user.

5. On the container, add /etc/sudoers.d/ubuntu with

   ubuntu ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

   This ensures 'ubuntu' can sudo without requiring a password.

6. On the container:

   `sudo apt-get install python python-apt`



